transcripts.text: With a purposeful grimace and a terrible sound, he pulls the spinning high tension wires down.  Helpless people on subway trains Scream by God as he looks in on them.  He picks up a bus and he throws it back down As he waves through the buildings toward the center of town.  Oh no, they say he's got to go for Bogazan.  Oh no, there's no stock here for Bogazan.  1, 2, 3.  Oh no, they say he's got to go, go, go, Godzilla!  Oh no, there goes Tokyo, go, go, Godzilla!  History shows again and again how nature points out the folly of man.  Godzilla!  Godzilla!  Godzilla!  Godzilla!  Godzilla!  History shows again and again how nature points out the folly of man.
